pastoral and georgic canon. Allowing for the sentience and sociality of this species makes it easier to imagine a natureculture within which to make kin across the species boundary. Reading poetry about sheep has the power to make new meanings as we try to adapt to an increasingly complex and problematic environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnimals in literature. 0aNature in literature. 0aPoetryxHistory and criticism. 0aSheep in literature. 4aLiterature Studies 2021. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Subjects & Themes / Nature .2bisacsh  aagro-pastoral societies.  aanimal studies.  aclimate crisis.  acultural landscapes.  aecocriticism.  apostcolonial poetry.  asheep in poetry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615658740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526156587423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526156587/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles